SIMPLE: persistency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Persistency
<hw>Per*sist"en*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Persistent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of
being persistent; staying or continuing quality; hence, in an
unfavorable sense, doggedness; obstinacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The continuance of an effect after the cause which
first gave rise to it is removed</def>; as: <sd>(a)</sd>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The <ex>persistence</ex> of motion.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Visual <ex>persistence</ex>, or
<ex>persistence</ex> of the visual impression; auditory
<ex>persistence</ex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persistent</ent>⟦br⟧
